1C 2S pass 2NT pass 3D pass 4S pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 20, chOption: S, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:2, nBasis: 0, nRot: 2, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "b4e8f0c7bbe2aa45580e3a796f12fba6c19c403cfeeeeb8856da4a899c7b73cd"]
[Category "Competitive Bidding"]
[Difficulty "beginner"]
[SkillPath "competitive_bidding/overcalls"]
[Student "S"]
{The bidding has been as shown.   

You might just try 4\S. Of course if partner has a minimum Weak Jump Overcall that will get you much too high. A better approach is to ask for more information from partner. The bid that asks is 2NT. Partner replies 3\D.  

Partner's 3\D bid tells you two things. One, he is in the top half of his 6-11 point range. Two, he has a high card (Ace or King) in \Ds. When you construct a hand for him which contains 6 pretty good \Ss and the \DA you come up with a hand which will probably make game. Bid 4\S.}

